Sec. 35, all, excepting therefrom the right-of-way of the Wabash Railroad and that part of the SW ¼ SW ¼ lying west thereof.
This refuge shall be known as the Swan Lake Migratory Waterfowl Refuge.
FRANKLIN D ROOSEVELT
The White House,
February 27, 1937.
